{"title":"{{< i18n requirements_doc >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n requirements_doc >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis document defines the **project requirements baseline**, capturing:\n\n- Business requirements\n- Environmental and ecological requirements\n- Functional requirements\n- Non-functional requirements\n- Governance and compliance requirements\n\nIt is a **mandatory PMBOK Planning artifact** and must be approved **before\nfinalization of the Project Management Plan (PMP)**.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements Guiding Principles\n\n1. **Ecological protection is the primary requirement**\n2. Automation must not compromise environmental confidence\n3. Human-in-the-loop validation is mandatory\n4. Requirements must be:\n   - Verifiable\n   - Traceable\n   - Testable\n5. No requirement is valid unless it supports **[OKR at section @sec-okr]**\n\n---\n\n## Business Requirements (BR)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Rationale | Acceptance Criteria |\n|-----|---------------|------------|-----------------|\n| BR-01 | Reduce manual screening effort for AUV imagery | Scale ecological analysis | ≥ 30% reduction in manual screening volume |\n| BR-02 | Reduce time to environmental insight | Faster ecological decision-making | ≥ 25% reduction vs baseline |\n| BR-03 | Preserve ecological confidence | Avoid loss of benthic data | ≥ 85–90% retention of true benthic imagery |\n| BR-04 | Enable reuse across fields | Dilute cost and effort | Demonstrated reuse in ≥ 2 fields |\n| BR-05 | Create reusable digital environmental assets | Long-term value creation | Assets versioned and auditable |\n\n---\n\n## Environmental & Ecological Requirements (ER)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description | Acceptance Criteria |\n|-----|-------------|--------------------|----------------|\n| ER-01 | Benthic relevance protection | Screening must prioritize retention of benthic-relevant imagery | KPI-3 ≥ threshold |\n| ER-02 | Human ecological authority | Final validation performed by environmental SMEs | SME sign-off |\n| ER-03 | Transparency of limitations | Model assumptions and limits documented | Validation report approved |\n| ER-04 | Consistency across fields | Ecological interpretation must be stable | KPI-4 within tolerance |\n| ER-05 | Auditability | Ecological decisions traceable | Full data lineage |\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements (FR)\n\n### Data Ingestion\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description |\n|----|---------|-------------------|\n| FR-01 | AUV image ingestion | Ingest still images from AUV campaigns |\n| FR-02 | Metadata ingestion | Capture temporal, spatial, and campaign metadata |\n| FR-03 | Batch processing | Support offline, batch-oriented workflows |\n\n---\n\n### Preprocessing\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description |\n|----|---------|------------------|\n| FR-04 | Image normalization | Normalize resolution and basic visual properties |\n| FR-05 | Quality filtering | Identify unusable frames (blur, severe turbidity) |\n\n---\n\n### Annotation & Validation\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description |\n|----|---------|------------------|\n| FR-06 | AI-assisted annotation | Support assisted labeling workflows |\n| FR-07 | Human-in-the-loop | Enable SME validation and override |\n| FR-08 | Iterative refinement | Support retraining based on SME feedback |\n\n---\n\n### Model Training & Inference\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description |\n|----|-----------|------------------|\n| FR-09 | Binary classification | Classify images as benthic-relevant or not |\n| FR-10 | Precision-oriented inference | Prioritize false-negative control |\n| FR-11 | Explainability support | Provide traceable outputs |\n\n---\n\n### Output & Asset Management\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description |\n|----|-----------|------------------|\n| FR-12 | Filtered dataset output | Produce curated datasets |\n| FR-13 | Versioning | Version datasets and models |\n| FR-14 | Traceability | Maintain lineage and audit trails |\n\n---\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description | Acceptance Criteria |\n|-----|----------|----------------|---------------------|\n| NFR-01 | Scalability | Handle TB-scale datasets | Successful batch processing |\n| NFR-02 | Offline-first | No dependency on real-time systems | Offline execution validated |\n| NFR-03 | Performance | Process within acceptable time | Meets KPI-2 |\n| NFR-04 | Reliability | Stable repeated runs | Consistent outputs |\n| NFR-05 | Security | Access-controlled data | Petrobras IT compliance |\n| NFR-06 | Maintainability | Modular pipeline | Code review approval |\n\n---\n\n## Compliance & Governance Requirements (CR)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Description |\n|----|---------|------------------|\n| CR-01 | Licensing compliance | Use only license-compliant AI frameworks |\n| CR-02 | Data governance | Align with Petrobras data governance |\n| CR-03 | Auditability | Full traceability for audits |\n| CR-04 | Environmental governance | Alignment with SUB environmental policies |\n| CR-05 | Stage-Gate adherence | Subject to KPI-based gates |\n\n---\n\n## Requirements Traceability (High-Level)\n\nEach requirement must be traceable to:\n\n- [OKR at section @sec-okr]\n- At least one executive KPI\n- One or more WBS elements (defined later)\n\nA formal **Requirements Traceability Matrix (RTM)** will be created during PMP\ndevelopment.\n\n---\n\n## Assumptions and Constraints (Reference)\n\n- No pre-labeled dataset initially available\n- Natural class imbalance exists\n- Offline-first constraint applies\n- Environmental SMEs availability assumed\n\n*See Assumption Log and Risk Register (@sec-risk-register) for details.*\n\n---\n\n## Approval and Baseline\n\nThis Requirements Specification becomes **baselined** upon approval.  \nChanges require formal change control.\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"f